Almond Croissant Blondes
  --Chahinez Tabet Aoul

Frangipane
4 tbsp butter
1/4 c granulated sugar
1 egg yolk
1/4 tsp vanilla 
1/4 tsp almond extract
1/4 tsp orange zest optional but helps elevate the croissant blondies
2/3 c almond flour
pinch of salt

Cream the butter, and white sugar sugar together. Mix in the egg yolk, orange zest, vanilla, and almond extract together. Fold in salt, and almond flour until a paste forms. Set aside.

Blondies:
1/2 c unsalted butter softened
1 c light brown sugar packed▢1 large egg at room temperature
1/4 tsp almond extract
2 tsp vanilla extract
1/4 tsp salt
1 & 1/3 c ap flour
1/4 tsp baking powder
1/3 c almond flour
1/2 c sliced almonds to top the blondies
powdered sugar for dusting

Preheat your oven to 350F and line a 8×8" baking pan with parchment paper. In a large bowl, mix the softened butter and brown sugar until well combined. Add the egg, and almond extract, and mix until smooth. Add the flour, baking powder, salt, and almond flour and stir until just combined. Do not over-mix. Spread the batter evenly into the prepared baking pan. top with the frangipane then swirl using a wooden skewer. Top with the sliced almonds. Bake for 30 min, or until the edges are set and the center is slightly firm. Allow the blondies to cool in the pan before dusting with powdered sugar, and slicing into squares.





